# Analysis Questions Answers

Q1. How does Django ORM simplify database operations?

Django ORM allows developers to interact with databases using Python code instead of SQL queries. It automatically generates SQL statements, reduces coding effort, improves readability, and provides database independence.

 Q2. What security considerations are crucial?

Authentication, authorization, CSRF protection, password hashing, input validation, file upload validation, and HTTPS.

 Q3. How can the platform scale?

Using caching (Redis), database optimization, load balancing, CDN, asynchronous tasks, and cloud deployment.

Q4. What features improve user engagement?

Likes, comments, notifications, messaging, personalized feed, and friend recommendations.

 Q5. How can content moderation be implemented?

User reporting, admin moderation panel, profanity filtering, AI-based spam detection, and content approval workflows.

